about.summary: JSON API(jsonapi.org) serializer that works with rails and can be used to serialize any kind of ruby objects

name: rb-fast_jsonapi
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "fast_jsonapi" %}
{% set version = "1.5" %}

package:
  name: rb-{{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://rubygems.org/downloads/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
  sha256: 22c88f388e4d275f87815b7818fb013a06d43fb7cdf893b72e89aae8e3e87613

build:
  noarch: generic
  number: 0
  script:
    - gem install -N -l -V --norc --ignore-dependencies {{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
    - gem unpack {{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
  skip: {{ win }}

requirements:
  host:
    - ruby
  run:
    - ruby
    - rb-activesupport >=4.2

test:
  commands:
    - ruby -r {{ name }} -e 'exit 0'

about:
  home: https://rubygems.org/gems/{{ name }}
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: {{ name }}-{{ version }}/LICENSE.txt
  summary: JSON API(jsonapi.org) serializer that works with rails and can be used to serialize any kind of ruby objects
  doc_url: https://www.rubydoc.info/gems/{{ name }}
  dev_url: https://github.com/Netflix/fast_jsonapi

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - oblute
    - benhuff
    - sodre
